stylometry: Safety stock is the extra inventory held in case the demand is larger than expected between the order time and the time the order arrives. It is used so that the company does not run out of stock if there is more demand. It is especially important when the demand level is at a unknown rate. it also helps with keeping the RQ model which is the Reorder point and Quantity level. Knowing when to reorder based on quantity already kept and demand is a little easier knowing their is safety stock available.
